   .

                             NO-SMOKING FLIGHTS

   .

   Effective June 4, 2000, smoking is banned on all scheduled passenger
   flights of U.S. airlines and on all scheduled passenger flights of
   foreign air carriers to and from the United States except for those
   flights of Aeroflot and of Egyptair for which the Department of
   Transportation has granted a waiver.


   Many airlines have prohibited smoking on flights not covered by the
   ban.  For detailed information, see(SMOKE-FREE AIRLINE FLIGHTS).
